--- Fully supported by  @{" LARRY CLOUD & KEITH TOWNSEND" link "11" 0} ,
@{" MEBBSNET © CSR Sites " link "12" 0}

--- Extremely @{" CONFIGURABLE " link "3" 0}
@endnode

@node "3" " How do I configure ListIt? "
 How do I configure ListIt?
 --------------------------

 ListIt is an AREXX © script for the MEBBSNET © BBS software.  You must
already have AREXX © @{"installed and running" link "13" 0} prior to attempting to run this
door.  It is NOT a door, however, as it runs independently of MEBBSNET.

You will need to create a directory where ListIt will place the data files and
catalogs. You can then put the ListIt program and icon in any directory that
you wish. It can then be run from workbench or CLI.

Next, open a shell, cd to wherever you put the files, and type LISTIT CONFIG
and follow the instructions.

Once you've configured it, you can put it in any script (LOGOFF, MIDNIGHT,
etc.) and run it as many times as you want.  It will only update files that
have changed since last execution, skipping anything unchanged.  The first
time you run it, it will take a while!  Be forewarned.  Once that initial
runthough is done, though, its lightning fast.


RUNNING LISTIT

Open a shell and type LISTIT.  Or double click on its icon.  Couldn't be
simpler.
@endnode

